薇兹必须让自己从情感上与电影中描绘的暴行中分离。“你要学会这点，”她说：“‘开始’和‘停’之间是真实的，‘停’之后就都不是真的了”<ref name="Leong" />。波克瓦克也有同样的感觉，并且进一步指出在警察部队时，有必要让自己从情感上与工作保持距离<ref name="Leong" />。另一方面，制片人希望能让观众受到片中那些被迫卖淫女性受到残暴对待的镜头影响，所以增加了拉亚一角，来给予这些受害人一张真实的面孔<ref name="CM">{{cite news | title = The Whistleblower (2010/2011) | work = Covering Media | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archivedate = 2013-12-27 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131227061359/http://www.coveringmedia.com/movie/2011/08/the-whistleblower.html | deadurl = no | url = http://www.coveringmedia.com/movie/2011/08/the-whistleblower.html }}</ref>。电影首次在多伦多放映期间，一位观众因片中的暴力镜头晕倒，大部分强奸的镜头因此遭到删减<ref name="Leong">{{cite news | last = Leong | first = Melissa | title = Star Rachel Weisz and subject Kathryn Bolkovac on detaching themselves from the events of The Whistleblower | work = The National Post | date = 2010-09-17 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140907081932/http://arts.nationalpost.com/2010/09/17/star-rachel-weisz-and-subject-kathryn-bolkovac-on-detaching-themselves-from-the-events-of-the-whistleblower/ | archivedate = 2014-09-07 | url = http://arts.nationalpost.com/2010/09/17/star-rachel-weisz-and-subject-kathryn-bolkovac-on-detaching-themselves-from-the-events-of-the-whistleblower/ }}</ref>。对此薇兹表示：
