=== 票房 ===
塞缪尔·戈尔德温影业购买了本片在美国的院线发行权<ref>{{cite news | last = Kit | first = Borys | title = Rachel Weisz's 'The Whistleblower' Picked Up By Samuel Goldwyn Films | work = The Hollywood Reporter | archivedate = 2013-12-29 | url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/risky-business/rachel-weiszs-whistleblower-picked-samuel-35825 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131229105252/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/risky-business/rachel-weiszs-whistleblower-picked-samuel-35825 | date = 2010-11-04 | accessdate = 2014-08-15 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。影片于2011年8月5日开始限量放映，最初上映的[[电影院|电影院]]只有7家，之后一度增至70家。影片一共在院线上映了12个星期，[[票房|票房]]总额112万4966美元<ref name="BoxOffice" />。

=== 专业评价 ===
电影发行期间所获评价褒贬不一<ref>{{cite news | last = Sandell | first = Scott | work = Los Angeles Times | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140714232635/http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/movies/2011/08/the-whistleblower-poster-child-for-the-middlebrow.html | title = 'The Whistleblower': Poster child for the middlebrow? | date = 2011-08-13 | deadurl = no | url = http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/movies/2011/08/the-whistleblower-poster-child-for-the-middlebrow.html | archivedate = 2014-07-14 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 }}</ref>。根据[[烂番茄|烂番茄]]上收集的115篇评论文章，其中有85篇给出“新鲜”的正面评价，“新鲜度”为74%，[[加权平均数|平均得分]]6.5（最高10分）<ref>{{cite news | title = The Whistleblower | work = Rotten Tomatoes | url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_whistleblower/ | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140429065058/http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_whistleblower/ | publisher = Flixster | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-04-29 }}</ref>。而{{lang|en|[[Metacritic|Metacritic]]}}上收集的30篇评论文章中则有17篇好评，3篇差评，10篇褒贬不一，平均得分59（最高100）<ref>{{cite news | title = The Whistleblower | publisher = Metacritic | work = CBS | url = http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-whistleblower | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140324075659/http://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-whistleblower | archivedate = 2014-03-24 }}</ref>。《[[卫报|卫报]]》的艾德·乌连米（{{lang|en|Ed Vulliamy}}）称《告密者》是“近年来最震撼人心的纪录风格剧情片”<ref name="Vulliamy" />，《[[赫芬顿邮报|赫芬顿邮报]]》的马歇尔·范恩（{{lang|en|Marshall Fine}}）称这是个“黑暗、严酷而惨痛”的故事<ref>{{cite news | last = Fine | first = Marshall | title = HuffPost Review: The Whistleblower | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131228082314/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/marshall-fine/huffpost-review-ithe-whis_b_919214.html | archivedate = 2013-12-28 | work = The Huffington Post | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | date = 2011-08-05 | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/marshall-fine/huffpost-review-ithe-whis_b_919214.html }}</ref>。《电影期刊国际》（{{lang|en|''Film Journal International''}}）的多丽丝·图马金（{{lang|en|Doris Toumarkine}}）称赞电影以良好的笔触讲述了一个令人感到不安的故事，给那些走进电影院、希望看到一部构思精巧、制作精良电影的观众们留下深刻印象<ref name="Toumarkine" />。[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]新闻网站{{lang|en|News.com.au}}的雷·帕奇（{{lang|en|Leigh Paatsch}}）表示，在薇兹成熟而专业的引导下，波尔瓦克与众多不公斗争的坚强信念让观众一直紧盯着银幕<ref>{{cite news | last = Paatsch | first = Leigh | title = Film review: The Whistleblower | publisher = News.com.au | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | url = http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/movies/film-review-the-whistleblower/story-e6frfmw0-1226152044553 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140221151824/http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/movies/film-review-the-whistleblower/story-e6frfmw0-1226152044553 | date = 2011-09-29 | archivedate = 2014-02-21 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。斯蒂芬妮·福斯特（{{lang|en|Stephenie Foster}}）在《赫芬顿邮报》上给予本片高度评价：
{{quote|这是个引人注目而且令人抓狂的故事，反映了国际机构各职能部门的复杂性和相互间的影响，以及在人们的所作所为可以拥有豁免权时应用问责制的困难程度。与此同时，这也是个有勇气的人在艰难环境下做出并不符合个人最大利益决定的故事。<ref name="Foster">{{cite news | last = Foster | first = Stephenie | title = The Whistleblower: A Compelling Film About Standing Up for What's Right | work = The Huffington Post | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131226072731/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/stephenie-foster/whistleblower-film_b_914881.html | url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/stephenie-foster/whistleblower-film_b_914881.html | date = 2011-08-02 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2013-12-26 }}</ref>}}
《巴尔干纪事报》也刊登了类似的正面评价：
{{quote|康达基在自己的前进方向上表现出了巨大的潜力。电影大部分的节奏都很紧凑，制作上的感觉也很精良……影片唯一让人不尽人意的就是结局。但这不是电影人的错，他们只是选择忠实于波克瓦克的故事。没有任何人受到正义的惩罚。只有为数不多的几个人遭到解雇并遣送回国，而且所有人都拥有外交豁免权，所以都无需面对刑事起诉。全世界还是有两百万人口贩卖的受害者。<ref>{{cite news |title=The Whistleblower – A film about the true story from Bosnia |work=The Balkan Chronicle |date=2012-03-20 |accessdate=2014-08-17 |archivedate=2013-12-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228053941/http://www.balkanchronicle.com/index.php/arts-a-culture/entertainment/movies/1282-the-whistleblower-a-film-about-the-true-story |deadurl=yes |url=http://www.balkanchronicle.com/index.php/arts-a-culture/entertainment/movies/1282-the-whistleblower-a-film-about-the-true-story }}</ref>}}

《[[影音俱乐部|影音俱乐部]]》的阿利森·威尔莫尔（{{lang|en|Allison Willmore}}）对《告密者》评价不佳，批评其中的反面人物塑造流于表面：“片中没有任何导致这一结果的道德侵蚀情况描写”<ref>{{cite news | last = Willmore | first = Allison | title = The Whistleblower | work = A.V. Club | url = http://www.avclub.com/review/the-whistleblower-59934 | date = 2011-08-04 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131228063519/http://www.avclub.com/review/the-whistleblower-59934 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2013-12-28 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 }}</ref>。《[[基督科学箴言报|基督科学箴言报]]》的彼得·莱纳（{{lang|en|Peter Rainer}}）认为电影的节奏太不平衡，让人感到沮丧，但还是称赞了演员的表演：康多雷克将拉亚的颤抖和恐怖描绘得活灵活现<ref name="Rainer">{{cite news | last = Rainer | first = Peter | title = The Whistleblower: movie review | work = Christian Science Monitor | url = http://www.csmonitor.com/The-Culture/Movies/2011/0805/The-Whistleblower-movie-review | date = 2011-08-05 | accessdate = 2014-08-16 | archivedate = 2013-12-27 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131227220534/http://www.csmonitor.com/The-Culture/Movies/2011/0805/The-Whistleblower-movie-review }}</ref>。斯蒂芬·霍尔登（{{lang|en|Stephen Holden}}）在《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》上写道，本片讲述的故事是如此反叛，几乎让人难以置信。把人口贩卖和腐败归为战争及其后果道德泥潭的附带损害，这样的结论实在令人郁闷<ref name="Holden" />。他称赞薇兹的表演是片中“最强劲的元素”<ref name="Holden" />。

演员表演总体得到了评论员的认可。《[[今日基督教|今日基督教]]》的卡梅林·考特尼（{{lang|en|Camerin Courtney}}）对主角与有妇之夫发生[[性关系|性关系]]感到失望，但仍称赞了薇兹的表现，认为她成功地塑造了这个性格上直截了当、对发现深感震惊的公务员。卡特尼还称赞瓦妮莎·雷德格瑞夫成功诠释了薇兹所需要的导师，给予她温暖和力量；大卫·斯特雷泽恩饰演的内部事务专员彼得·沃德也是他在同类电影中的最佳表现；拉亚作为年轻的受害人则让人感到心碎。<ref>{{cite news | last = Courtney | first = Camerin | title = The Whistleblower | work = Christianity Today | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131112200154/http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2011/augustweb-only/whistleblower.html?start=2 | url = http://www.christianitytoday.com/ct/2011/augustweb-only/whistleblower.html?start=2 | date = 2011-08-12 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archivedate = 2013-11-12 | deadurl = no }}</ref>《[[信使邮报|信-{}-使邮报]]》（{{lang|en|''The Post and Courier''}}）的史蒂夫·雷亚（{{lang|en|Steve Rea}}）称赞雷德格瑞夫扮演的配角马德琳·里斯“有力、高雅、严谨”<ref name="Rea" />。《[[旧金山纪事报|旧金山纪事报]]》的米克·拉萨尔（{{lang|en|Mick LaSalle}}）称赞薇兹从心理上准确把握了这个没有办法睁一只眼闭一只眼的女性角色<ref>{{cite news | last = LaSalle | first = Mick | title = 'The Whistleblower' review: truth improves it | work = San Francisco Chronicle | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | date = 2011-08-12 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131014220847/http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/The-Whistleblower-review-truth-improves-it-2335188.php | url = http://www.sfgate.com/movies/article/The-Whistleblower-review-truth-improves-it-2335188.php | archivedate = 2013-10-14 }}</ref>。雷克斯·里德也在《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》上称赞了女主角的“精湛演出”<ref name="Reed" />。

康达基在片中对暴行的描绘引起了争议。[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]]的鲍勃·蒙德罗（{{lang|en|Bob Mondello}}）认为这些场面如“醍醐灌顶”，但也觉得这方面描写应该各含蓄才好，现有情况已经对影片产生不利影响<ref>{{cite news | last = Mondello | first = Bob | title = A 'Whistleblower' Against International Injustice | publisher = NPR | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110810203219/http://www.npr.org/2011/08/05/138901142/a-whistleblower-against-international-injustice | url = http://www.npr.org/2011/08/05/138901142/a-whistleblower-against-international-injustice | date = 2011-08-04 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archivedate = 2011-08-10 }}</ref>。《今夜电影》（{{lang|en|''Tonight at the Movies''}}）的瑞恩·罗哈斯（{{lang|en|Ryan Rojas}}）认为这部电影坚韧不拔的同时又有些绝情，还告诫称某些镜头可能会让部分观众感到冒犯：“虽然这些镜头的确起到了增强事件恐惧感的作用，但这也让导演试图通过对影迷感官简单地进行冲击、直到他们麻木来赢得赞誉的做法变得太着痕迹，因为这些强奸、残害和谋杀的表现方式都非常令人感到不安”<ref>{{cite news | last = Rojas | first = Ryan | title = Movie Review: The Whistleblower – A graphically charged drama about real life human trafficking | work = Tonight at the Movies | url = http://tonightatthemovies.com/indexhold/?p=13970 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140817080412/http://tonightatthemovies.com/indexhold/?p=13970 | date = 2011-08-04 | deadurl = yes | archivedate = 2014-08-17 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 }}</ref>。{{lang|en|Crosswalk.com}}网站的克里斯蒂安·哈梅克（{{lang|en|Christian Hamaker}}）写道：
{{quote|这部电影几乎自始至终都很严酷，对于一个如此骇人听闻的主题来说可能看起来没有什么不妥，但对观众来说，效果就像一直被大锤敲来敲去。性交易人口贩卖不是好事，是非常坏的事！你明白了吗，或是你还想不想再多看几个人身或性暴力的镜头？别担心：《告密者》里这样的内容多的是。这里已经把残暴带入毫无理由的境界，所有这一切都只是为了表现出它试图解决的问题有多么恐怖。<ref>{{cite news | last = Hamaker | first = Christian | title = ''Whistleblower'' Tackles Human Trafficking | publisher = Crosswalk.com | date = 2011-08-05 | accessdate = 2014-08-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110924005635/http://www.crosswalk.com/culture/movies/i-whistleblower-i-tackles-human-trafficking.html | url = http://www.crosswalk.com/culture/movies/i-whistleblower-i-tackles-human-trafficking.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2011-09-24 }}</ref>}}

[[巴尔干半岛|巴尔干半岛]]一家基于互联网的报纸《巴尔干纪事报》（{{lang|en|''The Balkan Chronicle''}}）认为，本片中的暴力内容是有必要存在的，并且也没有为了耸人听闻而夸张化：“粉饰太平对任何人都没有好处。这部电影最大的优点就是其令人毛骨悚然的真实性。”<ref>{{cite news |title=The Whistleblower—A film about the true story from Bosnia |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228053941/http://www.balkanchronicle.com/index.php/arts-a-culture/entertainment/movies/1282-the-whistleblower-a-film-about-the-true-story |newspaper=The Balkan Chronicle |accessdate=2014-08-17 |url=http://www.balkanchronicle.com/index.php/arts-a-culture/entertainment/movies/1282-the-whistleblower-a-film-about-the-true-story |date=2012-03-20 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2013-12-28 }}</ref>。影片在波斯尼亚上映期间邀请了波克瓦克到现场讲话，据报告，她的经历获得了热烈回应，激起对20世纪末所发生事件的热烈讨论<ref name="Sivertsen" />。

